# Masternode Configuration File
# ==============================
#
# This file configures your masternodes for remote management.
# Place this file in your TWINS data directory as: masternode.conf
#
# Format:
#   alias ip:port privkey collateral_txid collateral_index [donation_address:donation_percent]
#
# Fields:
#   alias              - Friendly name for the masternode (no spaces)
#   ip:port            - External IP address and port (default port: 37817)
#   privkey            - Masternode private key (generate with: twins-cli createmasternodekey)
#   collateral_txid    - Transaction ID containing the collateral output
#   collateral_index   - Output index (vout) of the collateral (0-based)
#   donation_address   - (Optional) TWINS address to receive donation
#   donation_percent   - (Optional) Percentage of rewards to donate (0-100)
#
# How to set up a masternode:
#   1. Generate masternode key:      twins-cli createmasternodekey
#   2. Get collateral outputs:       twins-cli getmasternodeoutputs
#   3. Add entry below with your details
#   4. Start masternode:             twins-cli startmasternode alias false <alias>
#
# Example entries:

# Bronze tier masternode (1M TWINS collateral)
#mn_bronze 45.32.100.50:37817 93HaYBVUCYjEMeeH1Y4sBGLALQZE1Yc1K64xiqgX37tGBDQL8Xg 2bcd3c84c84f87eaa86e4e56834c92927a07f9e18718810b92e0d0324456a67c 0

# Silver tier masternode (5M TWINS collateral)
#mn_silver 67.219.107.45:37817 93WaAb3htPJEV8E9aQcN23Jt97bPex7YvWfgMDTUdWJvzmrMqey aa9f1034d973377a5e733272c3d0eced1de22555ad45d6b24abadff8087948d4 0
